scopecontent.p:
The collection includes extended correspondence from 
                George Bancroft (1800-1891), American historian and statesman (Box 3, Folder 4); 
                August Belmont (1813-1890), German-American politician, financier, and Folsom's successor as chargé d’affaires to the Netherlands (Box 8, Folder 4); 
                John Romeyn Brodhead (1814-1873), American historical scholar (Box 4, Folder 3); 
                Edward Everett (1794-1865), American politician, pastor, educator, diplomat, and orator (Box 2, Folder 4); 
                Albert Gallatin (1761-1849), Swiss-American politician, diplomat, ethnologist and linguist (Box 2, Folder 7); 
                Jared Sparks (1789-1866), American historian, educator, and Unitarian minister (Box 4, Folder 4); and 
                Peter G. Stuyvesant (1778-1847), Folsom's uncle through marriage (Box 4, Folder 5).

Includes material from 
                            Park Benjamin Sr. (2 letters); 
                            Hamilton Fish (2 invitations); 
                            Mr. and Mrs. Alexander J. Hamilton (2 calling cards); and a letter from 
                            Washington Hunt, governor of New York, 1851-1852.
